Cell["\<\
The distributions are somewhat similar, but the Trowbridge-Reitz distribution \
seems to have narrower peaks and longer \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]tails\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] across the entire range (except for the uniform \
distribution which is identical for both).\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.552790035157279*^9, 3.552790113168524*^9}, {
  3.5550927068029413`*^9, 3.5550927097294197`*^9}, {3.5561618231471252`*^9, 
  3.5561618747277613`*^9}}],

Cell["\<\
Finally, here\[CloseCurlyQuote]s an interactive plot comparing it to Phong:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.5527904011933804`*^9, 3.552790442942306*^9}, {
   3.55279150095575*^9, 3.552791502527265*^9}, {3.55482501932666*^9, 
   3.554825069580428*^9}, {3.554825279025922*^9, 3.5548252835419283`*^9}, 
   3.556161894170252*^9}],

