Cell["\<\
Experimenting with various values shows us that the value of \[Alpha]abc2 \
appears to control the shape, while the value of \[Alpha]abc1 controls the \
roughness. (They are not cleanly separated, so when varying \[Alpha]abc2 you \
need to change \[Alpha]abc1 to keep the same roughness.) \
Let\[CloseCurlyQuote]s see if we can fit Trowbridge-Reitz using ABC: \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.554495903853079*^9, 3.554495966369687*^9}, {
  3.555092824322179*^9, 3.555092854970907*^9}}],

